; This plugin determines the categories and their articles for the encyclopedia.
; Categories are listed in "encyclopedia" and their articles in sections of the same names.

; Flags can be used to alter the behaviour of specific articles.

; Tier flags ensure that random unlocks via memory sticks will primarily work through articles based on their relevance.
; By using this you can ensure that the player has access to early-game content long before that of the very late-game.
; However, tiers will do nothing to hinder progress at the occasional possibility of discovering late-game content early on.
; Whilst regular articles are always randomly unlockable, there is a 50% chance of selecting exclusively from tiered articles.

; Mode flags make available/unavailable an article based on whether a certain mode is in use.
; A value of "0" requires the mode not be used for the article to be available, and vice versa for a value of "1".
; For an article to be available regardless of the current mode, the absence of this flag altogether will suffice.
; The available mode flags are as follows: "azazal", "debug", "dev_debug", "ironman", "story" and "survival".

; Unlock flags remove the requirement of having to discover an article or randomly unlock it.
; This is extremely useful for tutorial-esque articles, such as those about achievements or features.
; Valuing the unlock flag at "0" has the same effect as if the flag didn't exist whatsoever.

; For any article which you add it is HIGHLY recommended to add texture description for it for reasons too long to list, even if it lacks an image.
; You can create this by looking in the /configs/ui/textures_descr/ui_pda_encyclopedia.xml file and following the existing examples.
